REMARK 400 COMPOUND                                                             
REMARK 400 1CHO                                                                 
REMARK 400 THE ALPHA CHYMOTRYPSIN MOLECULE IS COMPRISED OF THREE        1CHO    
REMARK 400 POLYPEPTIDE CHAINS WHICH ARE DERIVED FROM THE ZYMOGEN OF     1CHO    
REMARK 400 THID ENZYME BY EXCISION OF RESIDUES 14-15 AND 147-148. TO    1CHO    
REMARK 400 ASSIGN SEPARATE CHAIN IDENTIFIERS TO THE THREE CHAINS        1CHO    
REMARK 400 WOULD OBSCURE THID RELATIONSHIP AND SO THID WAS NOT DONE.    1CHO    
REMARK 400 CHAIN TERMINATOR RECORDS WERE INSERTED AFTER RESIDUES 146    1CHO    
REMARK 400 AND 245 TO INDICATE EXPLICIT TERMINI AND THE SPECIAL CODE    1CHO    
REMARK 400 EXC WAS USED IN THE SEQRES RECORDS TO DENOTE THE EXCISIONS.  1CHO    
